<item>
            <title>[MATH-1068] KendallsCorrelation suffers from integer overflow for large arrays.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1068</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For large array size (say, over 5,000), numPairs &amp;gt; 10 million.&lt;br/&gt;
in line 258, (numPairs - tiedXPairs) * (numPairs - tiedYPairs) possibly &amp;gt; 100 billion, which will cause an integer overflow, resulting in a negative number, which will result in the end result in a NaN since the square-root of that number is calculated.&lt;br/&gt;
This can easily be solved by changing line 163 to&lt;br/&gt;
final long numPairs = ((long)n) * (n - 1) / 2; // to avoid overflow&lt;/p&gt;</description>
